snippet.title: AR feat. A$AP Ant & SODUH - Pharrell (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
"Fresh out of the depths of New York City, buzzing producer AR has solidified himself as one of the new tastemakers of this emerging sound listeners are getting hip to today. In the midst of having records with the likes of Q Da Fool, Wifisfuneral, Thouxanbandfauni, + more, he crafts an instant banger with Baltimore stars, A$AP ANT & Soduh. The Marino Gang bossman has been connecting the dots with the rising local star and the duo glosses over the AR instrumental in effortless fashion with this single. Not only will the song will get its shine in the DMV area, but it will ensure that there is fresh content to come out of that talented region - Gregory Harris

snippet.title: Kenny B - "History" (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
"The Dallas/Fort Worth has become a gold mine in today's scene of Texas music. With producing the likes of Post Malone, Hoodfame Go Yayo, Yella Beezy, and more, DFW has certainly been one of the hotspots in the Lone Star state for talent and Fort Worth's buzzing young artist, Kenny B is certainly proving that in all ways. Recently signing a new deal with Alamo Records, Kenny B becomes Fort Worth first artist to be signed to a major label and he expresses his level of excitement to make his stamp in the game with his newest visual, "History". The Recka Filmz directed video showcases Kenny tearing the beat up with his running-off-the mill flow and Big Texas attitude. Delivering his own recipe of success, this video will establish Kenny's place in the new emerging wave of artists from the Lone Star State. - Gregory Harris"

snippet.title: Krimelife Ca$$ - Wuss Poppin (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
I don't know much about this kid except that he's from Brooklyn and this song goes hard as hell. 

https://www.instagram.com/krimelifecass/?hl=en
https://twitter.com/KRIMELIFECASS 

"Hailing from the depths of New York City, Krimelife Ca$$ has been making a way for himself to present some of the grittiest vibes that The Big Apple has to offer in their sound today. Differentiating himself from the likes of peers coming from the same area, Ca$$ uses his aggressive tone and slick lyricism to his advantage engage listeners and he rightfully does so with his latest video, "Wuss Poppin". The No Jumper premiered visual captures the Brooklyn native toting straps, throwing gang signs, and grooving effortlessly to the score of the video. 

The New York City boom that has brought out the likes of Cardi B, A Boogie with the Hoodie, Young MA, and more has shown listeners that NYC is on the rise once again with offering talented acts to the forefront. On the independent level of the city's scene, Ca$$ has to be mentioned in the conversation of artists who are from the city who aim to make a difference with their sound and who push the boundaries to showcase the youth-driven energy that's derived in their music.  - Gregory Harris"

The video captures Comethazine roaming and flossing effortlessly in the New York City famed streets of Chinatown and Little Italy. As Comethazine delivers an impressive lead role in the video, Lonewolf takes the cake with his off the wall edits and enigmatic after effects. 

If singles such as ‚ÄúMight Cop A Jag‚Äù and ‚ÄúShoot Me‚Äù served a purpose for Comethazine to lay a foundation for him to prosper, ‚ÄúPiped Up‚Äù will be one of the singles that'll take him over the edge of indie hip hop‚Äôs new star to the ascension of becoming an household name."
